@node INTRO "Introduction"

	@{b}Introduction@{ub}

	POP3Stat is a little Tool for checking if you have mail in your
	POP3-mailbox. I wrote it because I found it annoying starting
	a whole mailer just to look if I have some mail. There also
	exists the very usefull YGMail but it is in fact a YAM companion
	and you have to have YAM installed to use it and it is quiet
	hard to check many POP3-accounts at once. POP3Stat needs only
	the ixemul.library, the ixnet.library (always the newest, in
	these days (05-Sep-99) is V48 the state of art) and a MC68020 to
	be happy.

	Details can be found at @{" features " link feat}.

	@{fg shine}@{b}Caution!@{ub}@{fg text}
	POP3Stat is still in beta-status so you can expect many bugs! I'm
	using it quiet often and have no problems, but who knows what'll
	happen to you (/your Amiga)!

@endnode
@node FEAT "Features"

	@{b}Features@{ub}

	À Nearly as much POP3-accounts as you want.
	À Checking all or only one POP3-account.
	À Multiple Prefsfiles supported
	À If mails are found, you can simply put it out, return a
	  certain returncode, set an ENV-variable or start a program.
	À Do as much as like of the above actions, even none or all is
	  supported.

	Yes, I admit, that I've stolen some ideas from YGMail @{b}:-)@{ub}.

@endnode
