@node COMMANDLINE "Commandline"

	@{b}Commandline@{ub}

	The commmand-template for POP3Stat is:

	PREFS=PREFSFILE/K,ACC=ACCOUNT/K/N,ENV/K,RC/K/N,CMD/K,NE=NOECHO/S


	The arguments in detail:

	@{fg shine}PREFSFILE@{fg text}:
	  A prefsfile as described here: @{" " link prefs}.

	@{fg shine}ACC@{fg text}:
	  A number between 0 and the ammount of the pop3-account defined
	  in the prefsfile. Predefined is 0 and means all. If you
	  specify a invalid number, 0 will be used instead.

	@{fg shine}ENV @{fg text}:
	  The name of the ENV-variable that will be filled
	  with the amount of the mails if any are found
	  (only useful when checking just one pop3-account).

	@{fg shine}RC@{fg text}:
	  The return code that shall be return if mails are found.

	@{fg shine}CMD@{fg text}:
	  The program that shall be run when any mails are found (only
	  useful when checking only one pop3-account). It doesn't detach
	  a task so use "run" or an equivalent if detaching is wished.

	@{fg shine}NOECHO@{fg text}:
	  Surpress the statistics.

	@{fg shine}ABOUT@{fg text}:
	  Prints out some information.

@endnode
@node PREFS "The Prefsfile"

	@{b}The prefsfile@{ub}

	  The prefsfile consists of a first line, which containts the
	ammount of datarecord followed by the records:

	i.e.

	  3
	  pop3.host.com
	  login-name
	  password
	  pop3.anotherhost.com
	  another login-name
	  another password
	  pop3.thirdhost.com
	  third login-name
	  third password

	Simple eh :-)?

@endnode
